parts.text: React hooks like useState and useEffect were introduced in React 16.8 as a way to use state and lifecycle methods in functional components.
React Hooks are functions that let you use state and other React features in functional components.

web.title: React Reference Overview - React
web.snippet: React Hooks are functions that let you use state and other React features in functional components.

parts.text: useState is a React Hook that lets you add a state variable to your component.

web.title: useState - React
web.snippet: useState is a React Hook that lets you add a state variable to your component.
